SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3445
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE SCHMIDT.
7380H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 210, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to licensed child
care facilities.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 210, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 210.204, to read as follows:
210.204. 1. As used in this section, "local educational agencies" mean school
2 districts and charter schools that have declared themselves as local educational agencies.
3 2. A licensed child care facility enrolling a child who requires a medical provider
4 statement of special needs for child care shall do the following if parental permission is
5 provided:
6 (1) Refer the child's family to local educational agencies or private education
7 agencies to support the needs of the child and the child's family;
8 (2) Collaborate with local educational agencies or private education agencies to
9 ensure the needs of the child are met;
10 (3) Coordinate with local educational agencies for a specialized care plan when
11 the child reaches three years of age;
12 (4) Prepare a specialized care plan to ensure best practices for the child are
13 followed; and
14 (5) Provide training to child care facility staff members to support of the needs
15 of the child.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

